1
00:00:00,170 --> 00:00:01,730
There is a pain that is harder than death.

2
00:00:01,730 --> 00:00:02,910
It is not torture.

3
00:00:03,100 --> 00:00:04,060
It is not humiliation.

4
00:00:04,060 --> 00:00:05,480
It is when you know who killed your

5
00:00:05,480 --> 00:00:06,940
loved one, yet you must walk up to

6
00:00:06,940 --> 00:00:09,120
him, kneel down, and apologize for the dead.

7
00:00:09,350 --> 00:00:10,810
No sorrow is allowed, no anger is

8
00:00:10,810 --> 00:00:12,730
allowed, not even silence is allowed.

9
00:00:12,730 --> 00:00:13,990
Because silence itself is an

10
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:15,490
attitude, attitude is evidence,

11
00:00:15,730 --> 00:00:16,850
and evidence means death.

12
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:18,730
The only thing you can do is to

13
00:00:18,730 --> 00:00:20,570
suppress all hatred into a flawless

14
00:00:20,570 --> 00:00:20,990
smile,

15
00:00:21,230 --> 00:00:22,290
and live on day by day.

16
00:00:22,550 --> 00:00:23,910
Autumn, twenty-three A.D.

17
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,460
News spread from Wancheng.

18
00:00:25,460 --> 00:00:27,140
Liu Xiu's elder brother, Liu Yan,

19
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,480
was killed by Emperor Gengshi, Liu Xuan.

20
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:31,260
No trial, no battlefield, no

21
00:00:31,260 --> 00:00:32,280
dignified way to die at all.

22
00:00:32,410 --> 00:00:33,310
He didn't die in battle;

23
00:00:33,550 --> 00:00:34,390
he was disposed of.

24
00:00:34,710 --> 00:00:36,150
Like a piece that must be removed

25
00:00:36,150 --> 00:00:36,770
from the board.

26
00:00:37,150 --> 00:00:38,870
The charges were fabricated, and it

27
00:00:38,870 --> 00:00:40,450
was too fast for the execution of a

28
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:41,350
decorated general.

29
00:00:41,590 --> 00:00:43,370
Liu Xiu was leading troops away.

30
00:00:43,370 --> 00:00:43,870
Two months ago,

31
00:00:44,010 --> 00:00:45,510
he defeated four hundred twenty

32
00:00:45,510 --> 00:00:47,270
thousand with three thousand at Kunyang.

33
00:00:47,270 --> 00:00:49,130
The whole world was whispering his name.

34
00:00:49,130 --> 00:00:50,030
When he heard the news,

35
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:51,290
he was surrounded by Emperor

36
00:00:51,290 --> 00:00:51,990
Gengshi's men.

37
00:00:52,210 --> 00:00:53,110
Colleagues in name,

38
00:00:53,550 --> 00:00:54,950
but in reality, they were eyes

39
00:00:54,950 --> 00:00:55,670
watching him.

40
00:00:55,670 --> 00:00:57,190
He had to make a judgment in a very

41
00:00:57,190 --> 00:00:57,730
short time.

42
00:00:57,910 --> 00:00:58,950
How he reacted next

43
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,380
would decide his life or death.

44
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:01,730
He was twenty-eight that year.

45
00:01:01,950 --> 00:01:03,450
The longest endurance in Chinese

46
00:01:03,450 --> 00:01:05,330
history begins right here.

47
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,260
To tell this story clearly, we must

48
00:01:07,260 --> 00:01:08,140
go back to the start.

49
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:11,780
Liu Xiu was the ninth-generation

50
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:12,680
grandson of Liu Bang.

51
00:01:12,810 --> 00:01:13,410
In his time

52
00:01:13,710 --> 00:01:15,150
this lineage was worthless now.

53
00:01:15,470 --> 00:01:17,090
The Han Tui'en Decree eroded it

54
00:01:17,090 --> 00:01:18,130
over generations.

55
00:01:18,130 --> 00:01:20,010
By Liu Xiu's father, Liu Qin, he

56
00:01:20,010 --> 00:01:21,270
was just Nandun's magistrate.

57
00:01:21,450 --> 00:01:22,310
His father died early,

58
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,900
and the brothers grew up farming in

59
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:24,820
rural Nanyang.

60
00:01:25,150 --> 00:01:26,970
But Liu Xiu had an extraordinary brother.

61
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,880
Liu Yan was a born leader.

62
00:01:29,150 --> 00:01:31,130
Bold, generous, and unconventional,

63
00:01:31,550 --> 00:01:32,810
he loved befriending heroes.

64
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:34,530
He always spoke of restoring the Han.

65
00:01:34,530 --> 00:01:36,330
Such talk was treason under the Xin

66
00:01:36,330 --> 00:01:38,370
Dynasty, but Liu Yan was fearless.

67
00:01:38,370 --> 00:01:39,930
He felt destined for great things.

68
00:01:40,050 --> 00:01:41,290
Liu Xiu was more like a shadow.

69
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:43,110
Silent, cautious, and unassuming.

70
00:01:43,450 --> 00:01:44,170
He loved reading.

71
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:46,140
His ambition was to be a Zhijinwu

72
00:01:46,140 --> 00:01:47,120
and marry Yin Lihua.

73
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:49,570
A Zhijinwu led the capital's guards.

74
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:50,590
It sounded grand,

75
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,060
but it was just a prestigious

76
00:01:52,060 --> 00:01:52,780
military post.

77
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,540
One aimed for the throne, the other

78
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:55,440
for security chief.

79
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:57,270
Standing together, everyone thought

80
00:01:57,270 --> 00:01:58,610
the elder brother would be the one

81
00:01:58,610 --> 00:01:59,270
to succeed.

82
00:01:59,270 --> 00:02:01,590
Chaos erupted at the end of the Xin Dynasty.

83
00:02:01,930 --> 00:02:03,370
Rebel armies like the Chimei and

84
00:02:03,370 --> 00:02:04,270
Lulin erupted.

85
00:02:04,270 --> 00:02:05,830
Liu Yan seized the moment,

86
00:02:05,830 --> 00:02:06,910
revolting with his brother and

87
00:02:06,910 --> 00:02:07,730
Nanyang elites.

88
00:02:08,010 --> 00:02:09,910
Liu Xiu rode an ox into his first battle;

89
00:02:09,910 --> 00:02:11,190
he didn't even have a horse.

90
00:02:13,110 --> 00:02:14,530
Liu Yan was a formidable fighter.

91
00:02:14,530 --> 00:02:15,990
He was a gifted warrior and a

92
00:02:15,990 --> 00:02:16,930
charismatic leader.

93
00:02:16,930 --> 00:02:18,550
His army grew, and his prestige

94
00:02:18,550 --> 00:02:19,930
soared, so much that the Lulin

95
00:02:19,930 --> 00:02:20,910
leaders grew uneasy.

96
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:22,230
February, twenty-three A.D.

97
00:02:22,630 --> 00:02:24,630
Rebel forces gathered to choose an emperor.

98
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:26,930
By merit and fame, Liu Yan was the

99
00:02:26,930 --> 00:02:27,530
best choice.

100
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:29,010
But the Lulin army refused.

101
00:02:29,010 --> 00:02:30,750
They had no ties or loyalty to the

102
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:31,290
Liu family,

103
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:33,440
only a temporary alliance of convenience.

104
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:35,810
They wanted a puppet, not a strong ruler.

105
00:02:36,110 --> 00:02:37,850
If Liu Yan took power and then

106
00:02:37,850 --> 00:02:38,370
purged them,

107
00:02:38,710 --> 00:02:39,750
none of them would escape.

108
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:41,460
Choosing the weak Liu Xuan as

109
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:43,280
Emperor Gengshi, Liu Yan became

110
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,760
Grand Minister over the Masses.

111
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,340
top of the Three Excellencies.

112
00:02:46,340 --> 00:02:48,340
As civil head, he was the empire's

113
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,020
nominal leader.

114
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:51,360
Yet this title didn't fix the core issue.

115
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:52,950
It wasn't about the rank,

116
00:02:53,350 --> 00:02:54,970
but about what everyone could see:

117
00:02:55,290 --> 00:02:56,290
if Liu Yan wanted to,

118
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:57,540
he was more qualified for the

119
00:02:57,540 --> 00:02:58,600
throne than Liu Xuan.

120
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,880
Liu Xuan was propped up,

121
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:01,530
but Liu Yan earned his way there.

122
00:03:01,530 --> 00:03:03,210
These two types of legitimacy carry

123
00:03:03,210 --> 00:03:04,310
vastly different weight.

124
00:03:04,490 --> 00:03:05,590
A puppet emperor who was pushed

125
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:06,370
onto the throne...

126
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:08,070
...never fears external enemies the most.

127
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:09,810
External enemies can be fought together.

128
00:03:09,950 --> 00:03:11,190
He mostly fears the more

129
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:12,730
emperor-like man beside him.

130
00:03:12,730 --> 00:03:15,270
Liu Yan's very existence denied Liu Xuan.

131
00:03:15,270 --> 00:03:17,550
Worse yet, Liu Yan didn't hold back;

132
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:19,250
he always resented Liu Xuan

133
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:20,090
becoming emperor.

134
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:21,480
His words and actions showed no

135
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,320
respect for Liu Xuan.

136
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:23,980
He probably felt that with his own

137
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:24,840
merit and strength...

138
00:03:25,410 --> 00:03:26,510
...no one could touch him.

139
00:03:26,510 --> 00:03:26,970
He was wrong.

140
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,640
Lulin generals Zhu Wei and Li Yi

141
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,060
kept whispering in Liu Xuan's ear.

142
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:31,720
If Liu Yan isn't removed...

143
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:32,500
He'll be trouble.

144
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,320
Insecure, Liu Xuan heard this

145
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:35,480
often, turning murderous.

146
00:03:35,850 --> 00:03:36,890
They found an opportunity.

147
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,740
Citing a subordinate's misconduct,

148
00:03:38,740 --> 00:03:40,340
they summoned Liu Yan and seized

149
00:03:40,340 --> 00:03:41,020
him immediately.

150
00:03:41,490 --> 00:03:41,990
...and killed.

151
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:45,690
Upon hearing this, Liu Xiu was stuck.

152
00:03:45,690 --> 00:03:47,890
With little power, he had no way to resist.

153
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:49,730
His subordinates included spies

154
00:03:49,730 --> 00:03:50,990
planted by Emperor Gengshi.

155
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:53,100
Every move he made was under surveillance.

156
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:54,980
After Liu Xuan killed Liu Yan, the

157
00:03:54,980 --> 00:03:56,320
next person to be watched was him.

158
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:58,420
If Liu Xiu showed dissatisfaction,

159
00:03:58,420 --> 00:03:59,920
grief, or any signs of potential

160
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:00,320
revenge,

161
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:02,030
...he'd soon follow his brother.

162
00:04:02,420 --> 00:04:04,040
So Liu Xiu did what might have been

163
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:05,660
the most painful thing in his life.

164
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:06,900
He rushed to Wancheng.

165
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:07,810
He forwent mourning.

166
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,600
No memorial tablet, no word on the

167
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,900
body, he didn't even head back to

168
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:11,380
his tent.

169
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,580
He went to see Liu Xuan and knelt,

170
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:15,140
apologizing for his brother's crimes.

171
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:17,160
Stating Liu Yan acted improperly

172
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,500
and he failed to discipline him, he

173
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:19,340
asked for punishment.

174
00:04:19,730 --> 00:04:21,190
History books recorded his posture

175
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,030
during that audience...

176
00:04:22,150 --> 00:04:22,810
taking the blame.

177
00:04:23,150 --> 00:04:24,750
He took all the faults upon his own head.

178
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,040
He never mentioned the wrong.

179
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:27,750
These words, written about a man

180
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,210
who just lost his brother, every

181
00:04:29,210 --> 00:04:30,430
single word is like a knife.

182
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,450
He was so humble that Liu Xuan had

183
00:04:32,450 --> 00:04:33,450
no reason to kill him.

184
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:35,170
Liu Xuan prepared two plans.

185
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:36,910
If Liu Xiu caused trouble, he'd

186
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:37,530
handle him too.

187
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:39,750
But Liu Xiu's reaction was surprising.

188
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:41,710
His brother was just killed, yet he

189
00:04:41,710 --> 00:04:42,670
came to apologize.

190
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:44,620
Liu Xuan was unsure how to react.

191
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:46,340
He made Liu Xiu the Marquis of

192
00:04:46,340 --> 00:04:48,300
Wuxin, granting him a title but no

193
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:48,780
real power.

194
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,120
This wasn't a reward.

195
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,280
It was appeasement, and also a test.

196
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,060
After making him a marquis, he'd

197
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:55,380
see how the man moved next.

198
00:04:56,850 --> 00:04:58,230
After returning to his quarters, he

199
00:04:58,230 --> 00:04:59,010
didn't dare to cry.

200
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:00,400
Not just in public, he didn't even

201
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,700
dare to cry when alone.

202
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:02,860
He didn't know if there were ears

203
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:03,580
behind the walls...

204
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,520
Outside the tent, he ate, met

205
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:07,060
people, and handled official

206
00:05:07,060 --> 00:05:07,820
business normally.

207
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,910
As if the death didn't affect him.

208
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:11,430
The Book of the Later Han describes

209
00:05:11,430 --> 00:05:13,510
him then: 'Eating, drinking,

210
00:05:13,510 --> 00:05:14,710
talking, and laughing.'

211
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:16,060
Six characters.

212
00:05:16,470 --> 00:05:17,850
They capture the whole process of a

213
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:19,310
man crushing his own bones and

214
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:19,850
swallowing them.

215
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,560
In those months, grief itself was

216
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,440
evidence of a crime.

217
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:24,390
Stop and think about that scene for a moment.

218
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:25,670
His own brother was murdered.

219
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,840
The killer sat across, offering a toast.

220
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,880
He couldn't refuse or stop smiling,

221
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,520
and he couldn't let that smile crack.

222
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,400
He had to not only smile naturally

223
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,960
but convince everyone he had truly

224
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:35,420
let it go.

225
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,960
This wasn't just for a day or two.

226
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,160
This went on for months.

227
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,780
A performance for survival that

228
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:40,620
could never falter.

229
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:42,300
What sustained this performance

230
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,900
wasn't character or background.

231
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:44,870
It was judgment.

232
00:05:45,170 --> 00:05:46,430
It was his ability to make cold

233
00:05:46,430 --> 00:05:48,150
calculations even in extreme pain.

234
00:05:48,470 --> 00:05:49,450
Turning against them now...

235
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:50,190
...would be a dead end.

236
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,780
Crying now would be a dead end.

237
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,300
Letting anyone see his true

238
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:54,760
emotions would be a dead end.

239
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:56,410
Only by staying alive could there

240
00:05:56,410 --> 00:05:57,010
be a future.

241
00:05:57,350 --> 00:05:58,670
History has many examples.

242
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:00,450
Goujian slept on wood, Han Xin

243
00:06:00,450 --> 00:06:02,110
crawled through legs, and Sima Yi

244
00:06:02,110 --> 00:06:03,610
faked illness to fool Cao Shuang.

245
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:04,760
But when they endured,

246
00:06:05,010 --> 00:06:06,210
at least they had a moment of

247
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:06,690
solitude,

248
00:06:07,010 --> 00:06:08,390
a corner where they could grit

249
00:06:08,390 --> 00:06:09,530
their teeth unseen.

250
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,370
Liu Xiu lacked even that luxury.

251
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:12,890
His environment of endurance was

252
00:06:12,890 --> 00:06:13,650
fully exposed.

253
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:15,170
Any second of losing control

254
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:16,300
would cost him his life.

255
00:06:18,330 --> 00:06:19,790
During Liu Xiu's days in Wancheng,

256
00:06:19,950 --> 00:06:21,250
He made another decision that

257
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:22,410
disheartened his followers.

258
00:06:22,410 --> 00:06:24,130
He deliberately distanced himself

259
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:25,710
from those close to Liu Yan, with

260
00:06:25,710 --> 00:06:27,590
no meetings or contact, drawing a

261
00:06:27,590 --> 00:06:28,150
clear line.

262
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,060
Wasn't cold

263
00:06:29,330 --> 00:06:29,810
protection.

264
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:31,940
He saw Liu Xuan tracking Liu Yan's men

265
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:33,430
to determine the next leader.

266
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:35,070
If Liu Xiu kept associating with

267
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:35,530
these people,

268
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:37,190
it would tell Liu Xuan that this

269
00:06:37,190 --> 00:06:38,810
group still had a leader and might

270
00:06:38,810 --> 00:06:40,030
gather together again.

271
00:06:40,030 --> 00:06:41,790
He had to make Liu Xuan believe one thing:

272
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:43,990
After Liu Yan, none would follow.

273
00:06:43,990 --> 00:06:45,930
"Not daring to be first." These

274
00:06:45,930 --> 00:06:47,930
five words in history aren't humility;

275
00:06:47,930 --> 00:06:48,830
they're survival.

276
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:50,650
Disappointing his followers was

277
00:06:50,650 --> 00:06:51,550
better than a purge.

278
00:06:51,930 --> 00:06:53,510
So he bore all the pain alone,

279
00:06:53,910 --> 00:06:54,810
while making his brother's

280
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:56,190
followers think he was heartless.

281
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:58,310
Enduring the enemy's suspicion on one hand,

282
00:06:58,680 --> 00:06:59,820
and the heartbreak of his followers

283
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:00,240
on the other.

284
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,540
Some people looked down on him

285
00:07:01,540 --> 00:07:03,220
because of this, thinking Liu Xiu

286
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:03,980
was nothing special.

287
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,370
His brother was killed, yet he

288
00:07:05,370 --> 00:07:06,270
showed no reaction;

289
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:07,830
he wasn't cut out for greatness.

290
00:07:07,830 --> 00:07:09,090
Later, they realized they were

291
00:07:09,090 --> 00:07:10,070
wrong, terribly wrong.

292
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:13,530
When would this endurance ever end?

293
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:15,330
Liu Xiu waited for several months,

294
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:16,830
until Liu Xuan's guard slowly lowered.

295
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:18,250
Then he seized a chance and

296
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:19,310
volunteered for Hebei.

297
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,940
Hebei was no simple territory.

298
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:22,570
Away from the court, it was ruled

299
00:07:22,570 --> 00:07:23,510
by powerful clans.

300
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:25,170
Order shattered, anyone who could

301
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:25,950
restore the region,

302
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,470
could grow their own roots.

303
00:07:27,810 --> 00:07:29,290
Titled General Who Breaks the

304
00:07:29,290 --> 00:07:31,310
Barbarians, acting Grand Marshal,

305
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:32,930
holding the powers of the Grand Marshal.

306
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,440
He crossed the Yellow River to

307
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:36,300
pacify Hebei, yet was given very

308
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:37,240
few actual troops.

309
00:07:37,550 --> 00:07:39,030
not even a decent unit at all.

310
00:07:39,350 --> 00:07:40,790
Liu Xuan thought this was exile;

311
00:07:40,910 --> 00:07:42,530
Liu Xiu knew it was a chance to breathe.

312
00:07:42,850 --> 00:07:44,290
In Wancheng, his every move was

313
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:45,110
evidence against him.

314
00:07:45,290 --> 00:07:46,510
In Hebei, he could finally

315
00:07:46,510 --> 00:07:47,410
reorganize people,

316
00:07:47,780 --> 00:07:48,720
rebuild relationships,

317
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:50,330
and have his own judgment once again.

318
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:52,890
To Liu Xiu, the key to Hebei wasn't the land;

319
00:07:52,890 --> 00:07:53,910
it was distance.

320
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:56,910
Distance is space, and space is possibility.

321
00:07:57,190 --> 00:07:58,950
Endurance isn't about keeping one's

322
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:00,510
head down forever, but waiting for

323
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:01,550
the chance to look up.

324
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:03,710
This was Liu Xuan's greatest mistake.

325
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:07,890
Returning to the word "endurance,"

326
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:09,170
many people interpret it as a

327
00:08:09,170 --> 00:08:11,030
virtue, as if endurance itself is

328
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:12,250
worthy of praise. It's not.

329
00:08:12,350 --> 00:08:13,370
Endurance is never the goal;

330
00:08:13,370 --> 00:08:14,410
it's a means to an end.

331
00:08:14,730 --> 00:08:16,450
Those months Liu Xiu endured

332
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:18,010
weren't because of good character

333
00:08:18,010 --> 00:08:18,810
or a broad vision.

334
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:19,390
He endured

335
00:08:19,550 --> 00:08:21,010
because he maintained his judgment

336
00:08:21,010 --> 00:08:22,830
even in extreme pain, calculating

337
00:08:22,830 --> 00:08:24,370
the probability of life and death

338
00:08:24,370 --> 00:08:25,050
at every step,

339
00:08:25,230 --> 00:08:26,490
and the gain difference between

340
00:08:26,490 --> 00:08:27,510
acting now or later.

341
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:29,250
The truly terrifying person isn't

342
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:30,130
the one in a rage

343
00:08:30,410 --> 00:08:31,610
but the one who hates to the bone

344
00:08:31,770 --> 00:08:33,130
yet can still keep a smile in the

345
00:08:33,130 --> 00:08:33,750
right place.

346
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,490
The former is just venting emotions;

347
00:08:35,610 --> 00:08:37,270
the latter is already planning the future.

348
00:08:37,470 --> 00:08:38,830
Looking back at this path:

349
00:08:38,830 --> 00:08:40,430
suppressing his tears at the news,

350
00:08:40,430 --> 00:08:41,810
rushing to Wancheng, and kneeling

351
00:08:41,810 --> 00:08:43,490
to his enemy to apologize for his brother,

352
00:08:43,810 --> 00:08:45,410
taking a marquisate with no power

353
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,210
giving thanks for a great favor.

354
00:08:47,210 --> 00:08:48,790
For months after, eating and

355
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:50,110
laughing as if all was well.

356
00:08:50,570 --> 00:08:51,990
avoiding his brother's followers

357
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:53,760
convincing all he was useless.

358
00:08:54,110 --> 00:08:55,630
Finally, the moment Liu Xuan let

359
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:56,270
his guard down,

360
00:08:56,450 --> 00:08:58,330
Volunteering for Hebei, none were

361
00:08:58,330 --> 00:08:59,450
impulsive or resigned.

362
00:08:59,450 --> 00:09:01,230
Every step was on a blade's edge.

363
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:02,630
every misstep would have been a

364
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:03,050
dead end.

365
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:04,940
He traded months of humiliation for

366
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:05,420
his life,

367
00:09:05,630 --> 00:09:06,830
and now he's ready to trade that

368
00:09:06,830 --> 00:09:07,850
life for the whole world.

369
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:09,690
Wancheng taught him one thing:

370
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:10,940
survival is not victory.

371
00:09:11,270 --> 00:09:13,060
Survival is just earning the right

372
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:13,970
to place another bet.

373
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:15,500
Next stop, Hebei.

374
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:17,250
There's no emperor there to back him up,

375
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:18,860
no elder brother to pave the way,

376
00:09:19,060 --> 00:09:21,120
and no ready-made army at his command.

377
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,860
Only a fragmented land, a people

378
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:23,980
who don't know who to trust,

379
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:25,290
and a decision that's about to

380
00:09:25,290 --> 00:09:25,910
change everything.

381
00:09:26,210 --> 00:09:28,790
The true story of Liu Xiu is only

382
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:29,550
just beginning from there.

